definition: East Timor (officially Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste)
east/host (i.e. sitting on east side of guest)/landlord
Wen River in northwest Sichuan (same as 汶川)/classical name of river in Shandong, used to refer to Qi 齊國|齐国

sentences.english: The highest point of East Timor is Mount Tatamailau at 2,963m.
sentences.chinese: 东帝汶最高的山是塔塔迈劳山，约2963米。

sentences.english: Thousands of Timorese protested outside the Australian embassy earlier this year.
sentences.chinese: 今年早些时候许多东帝汶人在澳大利亚大使馆外抗议。

sentences.english: 1975 - East Timor declares its independence from Portugal.
sentences.chinese: 1975年，东帝汶宣告脱离葡萄牙独立。

sentences.english: And peace keepers have completed their training of Timorese police and soldiers.
sentences.chinese: 维和部队已经完成了训练东帝汶警察以及士兵的任务。

sentences.english: A group of fish swims by a pristine coral reef along East Timor's East coast.
sentences.chinese: 一群鱼儿游经东帝汶东岸的原始珊瑚礁。

sentences.english: Only one country, Timor-Leste, is worse at enforcing contracts.
sentences.chinese: 只有东帝汶一个国家在执行合同方面比印度差。

sentences.english: Yet except for tiny East Timor, the country remains in one piece.
sentences.chinese: 然而除了小小的东帝汶，这国家仍保持完整。

sentences.english: Annan hopes that China will continue to support the UN's reconstruction work in East Timor.
sentences.chinese: 安南希望中国继续支持联合国在东帝汶的重建工作。

sentences.english: East Timorese women stand in line as they wait to cast their ballots at a polling station in Dili April 9, 2007.
sentences.chinese: 东帝汶首都迪力一间投票所里，妇女排队等待投票。

sentences.english: East Timor will continue to staunchly support the One China policy.
sentences.chinese: 东帝汶将继续坚定奉行一个中国政策。

sentences.english: Xanana welcomed Tang to the independence ceremony of East Timor.
sentences.chinese: 古斯芒欢迎唐家璇前来出席东帝汶独立庆典。

sentences.english: The assassination attempt is a massive blow to East Timor.
sentences.chinese: 这起刺杀企图对东帝汶来说是一记巨大打击。
